text.tspan: Spanning Trees
(Undirected graph; arrows go both ways)
A spanning tree is a subgraph of a graph (some subset of vertices and edges)
satisfying the following properties
1. Has all the nodes of the original graph
2. Does not contain any cycles (sequence of edges from one node to the next
that ends up where it started)
3. Fully connected into one piece (I can find a path between any two nodes)
Other Properties:
1. For N nodes, it has N-1 edges
2. Adding any single edge creates a cycle
3. Removing any edge breaks the full connection
Algorithm To Build
1. Permute the edges in some random order
2. For each edge in this order, add the edge if it doesn't create a cycle.
Otherwise, skip the edge
3. Repeat step 2 until the tree is connected
